{"word":"ἐγγύθεν","slug":"ἐγγύθεν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐγγύθεν</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐγγύς'><el>ἐγγύς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>from nigh at hand</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>with Verbs of rest, <i>hard by, nigh at hand</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <el>ἐγγύθεν τινί</el> <i>hard by</i> him, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}